==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===


Incarnation

The doctrine that Jesus assumed human form in the person of and is completely both God and man.
A person or thing regarded as embodying or exhibiting some quality, idea, or the like: The leading dancer is the incarnation of grace.

